The Volunteers at the Nelson County Food Pantry located in Michigan, ND want the community to know.
     With the holidays arriving, they want to remind the community of the
food pantry benefits.  This pantry is available to all Nelson County
     The volunteers take great pride in providing this service and want
everyone to know it is available to them.
       The hours are Monday & Wednesday from 9:00 AM to 12:00 PM.  There is a
Commodity Program for ages 60 and older, just fill out the form.  There is also another form to fill out with monthly income and
family member/household information.  These forms are available at the
Food Pantry and at the Michigan City Office. Volunteers at the Food
Pantry include: JoAnn Hjelseth, Sherrie Kjorsvik, Betty Kroke, Debbie
Narum and Dick Vasichek.  Any of these volunteers will gladly share how
this program works or answer any of your questions.
      Many individuals from the area donate produce & financial assistance to
help keep this program available. People may come to the food pantry for
their needs in rotation of every two weeks.  This Food Pantry serves the
residents of Nelson County.
      The Nelson County Food Pantry is located at 322 State Ave, Michigan ND.
 Please use the west door.  Currently with the COVID-19, one person may
be admitted at a time, face masks required.  If you wish to donate
financial assistance their address is PO Box 148, Michigan ND 58259.
If you wish to donate food supplies, please drop off Mondays &
Wednesdays when they are open.
